               <msContents>
                  <summary>This very brief text entitled <title>Niṣāb Tajnīs al-Alfāẓ</title>,
                     alternatively entitle <title>Tajnīs al-Lughāt</title> (Puns in Languages)
                     contains a brief, versified vocabulary of Arabic, Eastern Turkish, and Persian
                     that explanains variant meanings of words rendered by altering diacritical
                     marks, a feature frequently employed in puns (paronomasia). Composed by a
                     certain <persName role="aut">‘Abd al-Raḥman</persName> which lead many to
                     missatribute the work to Timurid-era poet <persName role="dub"
                        key="person_90042997" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90042997/">‘Abd al-Raḥman
                        Jāmī (1414–1492)</persName>. An Nevertheless, it enjoyed considerable
                     circulation especially as printed editions. The text features a Persian
                     introduction and 21 <hi rend="italic">qiṭ‘ah</hi> (sections), all featuring <hi
                        rend="italic">ghazal</hi> (lyric) poems. The terms range from words for God
                     discussed in the initial section to imperative verb forms. </summary>

                  <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_598-item1">
                     <author key="">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">‘Abd al-Raḥman</persName>; <lb/>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">عبد الرحمن</persName>
                     </author>
                     <author role="dub" key="person_90042997" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/90042997/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Jāmī, ‘Abd al-Raḥman ibn
                           Aḥmad, 1414-1492</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">جامى، عبد الرحمن ابن احمد‏</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22371">Niṣāb Tajnīs al-Alfāẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_22371">نصاب تجنيس الالفاظ</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22371">Tajnīs
                        al-Lughāt</title>
                     <title type="alt" xml:lang="ar" key="work_22371">تجنيس اللغات</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa" type="basmalla"><locus from="1b" to="1b"> برگ ۱پ (folio
                           1b):</locus> بنام خالق افلاک و توده عنبر * که نیست مخفی و پیدا خبر او
                        خدای ذکر. </incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ota"><locus from="8b" to="8b"> برگ ۱پ (folio 8b):</locus>
                        اخف دان دیور و یا سورمه دیو نهان کن * ار کورسان دیو مهنی کووسان بنما. </explicit>
                     <colophon>No colophon</colophon>

                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar chg">Persian, Arabic, and Chagatai
                        Turkish</textLang>
                     <note>For a description of the work and the spurious attribution to Jāmī, see Storey and Perry.
                        Chetham Librarian <persName role="edt" key="person_92189357"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/92189357/">Rev. John Haddon Hindley</persName>
                        of Manchester published a revised and expanded second edition of the English
                        translation by <persName role="trl" key="person_122281196"
                           ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/122281196/">F. Gladwin</persName> in <date
                           calendar="#Gregorian" when="1811">1811</date>.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
