                        calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1700" notAfter="1800">18th century
                        CE</origDate>.</origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>Subsequently acquired by <persName type="supplied" key="person_f830"
                           role="fmo" change="#role-assignment">Colonel George William Hamilton
                           (1807-1868)</persName> from an unidentified source. He served in
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7000208"
                           key="place_7000208">India</placeName> from <date calendar="#Gregorian"
                           from="1823" to="1867">1823 to 1867</date>, latterly as Commissioner in
                           <placeName ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001535"
                           key="place_7001535">Delhi</placeName>. He acquired over a thousand Indian
                        and Persian manuscripts, from which the <orgName
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/134857252">British Museum</orgName> purchased
                        352 from his widow, <persName key="person_f8470" role="fmo">Charlotte Logie
                           Hamilton (1817–1893)</persName>, now held in the <orgName
                           ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/121814978">British Library</orgName>.</p>
                  </provenance>
